# aspectratio.dev — Build & Execution Plan (Phase-by-Phase)

> Companion to `product.md`. That file is **what** we're building. This file is **how and in what order** — every phase, every workstream, in detail. No code here on purpose; this is the playbook you (or Claude Code) follow.

---

## How to read this document

Each phase is broken into the same **six workstreams** so nothing falls through the cracks:

1. **Architecture & infra** — the plumbing decided/built in this phase.
2. **Design & UX** — what gets designed or refined.
3. **Build** — the actual tools/pages/components shipped (described, not coded).
4. **Content & SEO** — pages, copy, schema, indexing rules.
5. **Analytics & QA** — what we measure and how we verify quality.
6. **Monetization & growth** — ads, affiliate, links, Pro/API (only where relevant).

Every phase ends with **Exit criteria** (the bar to move on), **Out of scope** (the scope guard — what we deliberately do NOT do yet), and **Risks**.

