## Cross-cutting rules (apply in every phase)

- **Speed is a gate, not a goal.** No page ships if it breaks the performance budget (LCP < 1.5s, CLS < 0.05, INP < 150ms, Lighthouse mobile ≥ 95).
- **A page exists only if it carries a real tool + unique content.** No empty doorway pages, ever.
- **Privacy by default.** Image work stays client-side; say so on-page.
- **One interactive color (teal), gold used rarely.** Design discipline holds across every new page.
- **Indexing tier is decided at creation**, not after — every new page is tagged Tier 1 / 2 / 3 and gets the right robots/sitemap treatment immediately.

