# Phase 0 — Foundation

**Goal:** Lay every rail so that from Phase 1 on, building a new tool page is fast, consistent, and automatically SEO- and performance-correct. Nothing user-facing ships yet except maybe a holding page.

**Why first:** Decisions made here (tokens, page template, schema helpers, analytics events) get reused on every page forever. Getting them right once saves rework on hundreds of pages later.

### Architecture & infra
- Stand up the Astro + TypeScript (strict) project with static output; pick the host (Cloudflare Pages) and wire CI so every push deploys a preview.
- Decide the island strategy: Astro for static shell, Preact islands for interactivity, nanostores for any cross-island shared state. Document when something is "static" vs "an island."
- Set up the content layer: define the typed collections (ratios, devices, resolutions, platforms, paperSizes) with their validation schemas. Even if data is sparse now, the shapes are locked.
- Create the shared library boundary: a single pure-function math module (ratio simplify, nearest-ratio, resize, PPI) that everything imports. Pure, testable, no UI.
- Install performance/SEO infra: sitemap generation with tier-aware exclusion, off-main-thread loading for third-party scripts, image/asset pipeline, font subsetting.

### Design & UX
- Finalize the design system from `product.md` into a living reference: the full color token set (stone neutrals, teal, gold, semantic), typography (Geist + Geist Mono, tabular numbers), spacing/radius/shadow/motion scales, dark + light themes.
- Build the core component inventory as designs/specs: buttons, inputs with inline copy, segmented control, the animated proportion-preview rectangle, drop zone, crop canvas shell, compatibility cell, result-stat, FAQ accordion, breadcrumb, related-tools module, code block, theme toggle.
- Design the **universal page template** once: header → H1 → intro → tool slot → "common results" link strip → explainer → FAQ → related tools → last-updated → footer. Every future page is a fill-in of this.
- Verify contrast for both themes and define the reduced-motion behavior.

### Content & SEO
- Build the SEO helper layer conceptually: per-page title/description templating, canonical logic, JSON-LD builders for WebApplication/SoftwareApplication, FAQPage, BreadcrumbList, HowTo, ItemList.
- Set the indexing policy in code: a page declares its tier and the system applies the correct robots meta + sitemap inclusion automatically.
- Plan the sitemap index split (tools / guides / locales) even before there's much to put in it.
- Draft the keyword cluster map (from `product.md` §7.0) into a working backlog: every planned page mapped to its head term and intent.

### Analytics & QA
- Wire privacy-friendly analytics off the main thread.
- Implement the event taxonomy as a typed helper so events are consistent from day one: preset_select, dimension_input, copy_dimensions, image_upload, crop_export, faq_expand, next_tool_click, etc.
- Establish the QA checklist (the Definition of Done from `product.md` §15) as the gate every page must pass.
- Connect Search Console + the analytics dashboard; set up Core Web Vitals monitoring.

### Monetization & growth
- Nothing live. But: reserve the ad-slot dimensions in the page template now (empty, fixed-size containers) so adding ads later causes zero layout shift. Decide affiliate partners to approach later (Canva, Adobe Express, CapCut, stock).

### Exit criteria
- A new blank tool page can be created from the template in minutes and automatically gets correct theming, SEO meta, schema, analytics hooks, and tier handling.
- Design system and component specs are approved and documented.
- Math module exists and is unit-tested.
- A throwaway demo page scores ≥ 95 Lighthouse mobile with the template + a placeholder tool.

### Out of scope (don't do yet)
- Any real tool logic, any indexable content pages, any ads, any data-heavy collections fully populated.

### Risks
- **Over-engineering the foundation.** Cap Phase 0 at 2 weeks. The template + tokens + math module + analytics are enough; resist building abstractions for features that don't exist yet.

