# Phase 1 — Hero Tools MVP (the launchable product)

**Goal:** Ship the three tools that *are* the product's reason to exist, polished to "best on the internet" quality, on a handful of beautifully executed pages. This is the version you can actually launch and start earning links/traffic with.

**Why now:** These are the link-worthy, screenshot-worthy tools that earn the authority everything else depends on. They must be excellent before anything is scaled.

### Architecture & infra
- Implement the math module's full surface for ratios: simplify via GCD, decimal, orientation, nearest-common-ratio ranking with % difference and confidence.
- Build the client-side image pipeline: read a dropped/selected file entirely in the browser (Canvas), extract resolution/type/size, never upload. Render crop/padding/letterbox previews on canvas.
- Wire shared state so width/height entered in the calculator can flow into the visualizer and vice versa.

### Design & UX
- Design and refine the **Universal Calculator** experience: live on-keystroke results, mode switch (W×H→ratio / ratio+one dimension→other / lock-ratio scaling), preset chips for the common ratios, the animated proportion-preview rectangle, copy-on-every-value.
- Design the **Image Analyzer + Compatibility Grid**: the upload affordance, the result panel (resolution, ratio, orientation, file size/type), and the platform-compatibility grid using the green/amber/red semantics (fits / needs crop / wrong shape) with exact target numbers and a one-click jump into the crop view.
- Design the **Crop / Padding / Letterbox Visualizer**: draggable, ratio-locked crop box over the user's real image; padding mode with background color/blur; letterbox mode with bar thickness readout; export/download of the result. Keyboard-operable crop box.
- Polish micro-interactions: number cross-fades, springy crop drag, copy confirmations, empty/error states (bad file type, huge file).

### Build (pages shipped)
- Home (`/`) — leads with the universal calculator and routes to the hero tools.
- `/calculator` — the canonical calculator hub (calculator + nearest-ratio).
- `/image` — analyzer + compatibility grid (+ optional single-image compress/export).
- `/crop` — the visualizer.
- `/resize` — resize without distortion + convert-to-target with crop-vs-pad recommendation + vertical converter.

### Content & SEO
- Write genuinely useful, unique on-page content for each hero page following the template: what the tool does, who it's for, real examples, 3–6 FAQs.
- Emit correct schema per page (WebApplication + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList; HowTo on resize/crop).
- Generate dynamic OG images that visually show the ratio/dimensions — these drive share CTR.
- All five pages are Tier 1: indexable, in the sitemap, hand-quality.

### Analytics & QA
- Fire the relevant events (dimension_input, preset_select, copy_dimensions, image_upload, compatibility_view, crop_export).
- Run the full DoD gate on every page: works, fast, accessible, correct schema, CWV green, both themes verified.
- Cross-device/browser test the upload + canvas flows (mobile Safari is the usual troublemaker).

### Monetization & growth
- No ads yet — protect the launch experience. Prepare the launch assets (Product Hunt, a short demo clip of the crop visualizer, dev-community posts). The crop/compatibility tools are the hook; lead with them.

### Exit criteria
- All five pages live, each passing the DoD and the performance budget.
- The crop visualizer and compatibility grid feel demonstrably better than any incumbent — the "would I screenshot/share this?" test passes.
- Launch posts ready.

### Out of scope (don't do yet)
- Programmatic ratio pages, device databases, platform-size pages, ads, Pro, API.

### Risks
- **Canvas/mobile bugs** eating time — budget explicit cross-device QA.
- **Scope creep into Phase 2** ("just one more dev tool") — hold the line; ship the five.

