# Phase 2 — Developer Cluster + Tier 1 Ratio Pages + Distribution Assets

**Goal:** Own the lower-competition developer/designer search cluster (the `.dev` advantage), hand-build the core per-ratio pages, and ship the two biggest distribution engines: the embeddable widget and an open-source npm package.

**Why now:** Devs *link to* free dev tools, and dev queries are easier to rank for than social-media terms dominated by huge brands. This is where early authority comes from.

### Architecture & infra
- Build the small dev-tool islands behind one shared pattern (input → generated output → copy button → explainer).
- Build the embeddable-widget delivery: a lightweight, themeable iframe build of the calculator/ratio tools served from `/embed/*`, with a copy-paste snippet and a "powered by" backlink.
- Package the core ratio math as a standalone open-source library + CLI (separate repo), published to npm under the brand.

### Design & UX
- Design the dev-cluster page style: code-forward, mono output, prominent copy buttons, syntax-highlighted result blocks.
- Design the embed widget's compact, responsive, themeable layout (light/dark, accent options) and the "get embed code" UX.
- Design the per-ratio page layout (a focused calculator pre-loaded to that ratio + ratio-specific content).

### Build (pages shipped)
- Dev cluster: CSS `aspect-ratio` generator, Tailwind class generator, SVG viewBox calculator, React/Preact component snippet.
- CSS-units cluster: px↔rem, px↔em, px→pt, px→vh/vw (with configurable root size/viewport).
- Hand-built `/ratio/[ratio]` pages for the ~6 core ratios (16:9, 4:3, 21:9, 9:16, 1:1, 3:2): unique copy, use cases, common conversions, FAQs.
- `/embed/*` widget endpoints.
- Public npm package + its docs/readme.

### Content & SEO
- Write distinct, substantive copy per dev tool and per ratio page (no templated thin text — each ratio has real, different use cases and examples).
- Internal-link the cluster tightly: ratio pages ↔ calculator ↔ dev tools ↔ comparison (when it lands).
- Schema: SoftwareApplication + FAQPage + Breadcrumb across the cluster.
- All Tier 1 — indexable, hand-quality.

### Analytics & QA
- Track copy_dimensions/copy_ratio, embed_copy, next_tool_click to see which tools drive recirculation.
- QA the embed widget across host-site contexts (different page widths, CSP, dark/light parents).

### Monetization & growth
- **This is the link-building phase.** Launch the npm package and embed widget publicly. Outreach to web-dev communities, design blogs, "free dev tools" roundups, Product Hunt. Submit to relevant tool directories.
- Still no ads — keep the dev experience pristine while you're courting links.

### Exit criteria
- Dev + CSS-units clusters and 6 ratio pages live and passing DoD.
- Embed widget works cleanly on third-party sites; npm package published with docs.
- First wave of organic backlinks/mentions appearing.

### Out of scope
- Ads, Pro, API, programmatic conversion pages, full device DB.

### Risks
- **Thin per-ratio pages.** If you can't write genuinely different content for a ratio, don't ship that page yet. Six excellent pages beat twenty thin ones.

