# Phase 3 — Reference Databases + PPI/Print Cluster + Tier 2 Platform Pages

**Goal:** Add the reference content that creates large, genuinely-useful surface area (devices, resolutions, print) and begin the social-media land grab via Tier 2 platform-size pages — each carrying a live tool, not just a number.

**Why now:** With authority building, you can responsibly expand into higher-volume, more competitive terms. Reference data and the print cluster also produce strong linkable assets.

### Architecture & infra
- Populate the devices, resolutions, and paperSizes collections with clean, sourced data.
- Build reverse-lookup logic (dimensions → device/resolution) and search/filter over the databases.
- Build the PPI/print math (density, physical↔pixel at DPI, paper size at DPI tables) on top of the shared math module.
- Build the platform-size page generator that pulls from the platforms collection and embeds a live "size/check/resize for this platform" tool.

### Design & UX
- Design the database browse/search experience (fast filtering, deep-link from any row into the calculator).
- Design the PPI/print pages and the **printable DPI chart** asset (paper sizes at every DPI) to be clean enough that people want to cite/print it.
- Design the comparison tool (overlay/side-by-side of multiple ratios at shared area or width, with shareable URL state).
- Design the platform-size page layout so the live sizer is the hero, with the reference numbers and platform notes supporting it.

### Build (pages shipped)
- `/devices` + `/devices/[device]`, `/resolutions`.
- PPI/print cluster: PPI calculator, pixels↔inches, cm→pixels, paper-size pages.
- `/compare` comparison tool.
- Tier 2 platform-size pages (start with the highest-value: YouTube thumbnail, Instagram reel/story, LinkedIn banner, X header), released gradually.

### Content & SEO
- Each platform page gets unique, useful copy + the live sizer + FAQs — this is what makes it Tier 2 (substantive) not Tier 3 (thin).
- Reference pages use ItemList schema where appropriate.
- Release platform pages in small batches; monitor which gain traction in Search Console before adding more.
- Heavy internal linking: platform pages ↔ image analyzer ↔ crop ↔ resize ↔ ratio pages.

### Analytics & QA
- Track compatibility_view, crop_export from platform flows, and which platform pages convert to tool use.
- Watch indexation and impressions per batch; prune or improve any page that stalls.

### Monetization & growth
- Distribute the printable DPI chart and reference assets for links (teacher/school resource pages, design blogs).
- Begin lining up affiliate relationships now (you'll place them in Phase 4 on exactly these platform/resize pages, where intent is commercial).

### Exit criteria
- Device/resolution/print clusters live; comparison tool live; first batch of platform pages indexed and gaining impressions.
- At least one reference asset earning external links.

### Out of scope
- Tier-3 conversion pages still `noindex`. API and localization not yet.

### Risks
- **Stale or wrong device/resolution data** erodes trust — source carefully and date it.
- **Platform pages drifting toward thin** — enforce the "live tool + unique copy" rule per page.

