# Phase 4 — Monetization (without wrecking the experience)

**Goal:** Turn the now-meaningful traffic into revenue through a clean ad layout, contextual affiliate, and a Pro tier — while keeping CWV green and the tools unobstructed.

**Why now:** Only monetize once there's traffic and the experience is proven. Ads added too early suppress the engagement/links that actually grow the site.

### Architecture & infra
- Load ads through the off-main-thread path so they don't tank INP/LCP.
- Implement the Pro tier: auth, billing, gated features (batch analyzer, batch export, AI crop suggestions, no-ads, saved presets/projects).
- Build the batch analyzer (upload many images → table of dimensions/ratios/compatibility → CSV export) as the flagship Pro feature.

### Design & UX
- Place ads per the placement map: one in-content unit below the fold after the first result, one desktop right-rail, one anchor unit — all in the fixed reserved slots from Phase 0 so there's zero layout shift. Never above the tool/preset chips.
- Design the Pro upgrade surface (clean, honest, value-led) and the affiliate placements so they read as helpful recommendations, not banners.
- Design the batch analyzer UI and the "remove ads / go Pro" affordances.

### Content & SEO
- Add contextual affiliate placements on commercial-intent pages (platform/resize/print) — Canva, Adobe Express, CapCut, stock libraries.
- Ensure ad/affiliate additions don't change page intent or trigger layout shift; re-run CWV on every monetized template.

### Analytics & QA
- Track pro_cta_click, upgrade conversion, affiliate clicks, ad viewability, and the effect of ads on engagement/CWV.
- A/B ad density and placement; pull back anything that hurts engagement more than it earns.

### Monetization & growth
- Revenue model as a planning frame: ~$6–11 page RPM on ratio/print intent, ~$4–7 on lower-CPC utility; treat affiliate + Pro + API as the upside, AdSense as the floor.
- Begin building the Pro funnel (batch use case targets agencies/creators).

### Exit criteria
- Ads live with zero CLS and CWV still green; affiliate placements live on commercial pages; Pro tier launched with a working batch analyzer.
- First revenue flowing; engagement metrics not degraded by ads.

### Out of scope
- Don't gut the free experience to push Pro. Don't add above-the-fold ads. Don't monetize the dev cluster aggressively (it's your link engine — keep it clean).

### Risks
- **Ads hurting CWV → ranking loss → less ad revenue** (the death spiral). Monitor CWV continuously; ads are the first thing to cut if vitals slip.

