# Phase 6 — Growth Loop (ongoing, never "done")

**Goal:** Treat the live product as a system to continuously measure, prune, and expand. This is the steady-state operating rhythm after Phase 5.

### The recurring loop
- **Measure:** weekly review of Search Console (impressions, positions, CWV, rich results) and analytics (tool completion, copy/export, recirculation, conversion).
- **Prune:** kill or merge pages that don't earn impressions/engagement after their grace period. Fewer strong pages > many weak ones.
- **Expand:** add the next tool/cluster/locale only when data shows demand and the previous batch is healthy.
- **Defend CWV:** re-test after every change; performance regressions are treated as bugs.
- **Earn links continuously:** new linkable assets (charts, widgets, open-source updates), ongoing community presence — never paid/spam links.
- **Refresh trust signals:** keep "last updated" dates honest, keep device/resolution data current.

### Family expansion (optional, beyond aspectratio.dev)
- The wider plan's heavier tools — **online ruler** (auto-detect → credit-card calibration → manual, as a guided three-state flow) and **measure-image-size** — are best as their own sister properties, cross-linked to aspectratio.dev rather than merged into it. Spin them up using the same foundation (design system, math/units modules, SEO template) once the core site is healthy.

### Ongoing risks to watch
- Google core/spam updates (keep content people-first, keep pruning thin pages).
- Ad density creep (guard the experience that earns the traffic).
- Data drift (devices/resolutions/platform sizes change — schedule refreshes).

